(43, 'P7N695', '"Study was the cry that reverberated in the corridors of my mind. Study to enable yourself to face the arguments advanced by opposition. Study to arm yourself with arguments in favor of your cult."\r\n- Bhagat Singh', 'Daljeet Singh', 'daljeet.working@gmail.com', '127.0.0.1', 1, '2013-11-23 20:11:12', '2013-11-23 20:11:12'),
(44, 'K7N695', 'The elimination of force at all costs is Utopian and the new movement which has arisen in the country and of whose dawn we have given a warning is inspired by the ideals which Guru Gobind Singh and Shivaji, Kamal Pasha and Reza Khan, Washington and Garibaldi, Lafayette and Lenin preached.', 'Daljeet Singh', 'daljeet.working@gmail.com', '127.0.0.1', 1, '2013-11-23 20:11:38', '2013-11-23 20:11:38'),
(45, 'J7N695', 'Non-violence is backed by the theory of soul-force in which suffering is courted in the hope of ultimately winning over the opponent. But what happens when such an attempt fail to achieve the object? It is here that soul-force has to be combined with physical force so as not to remain at the mercy of tyrannical and ruthless enemy.', 'Daljeet Singh', 'daljeet.working@gmail.com', '127.0.0.1', 1, '2013-11-23 20:12:05', '2013-11-23 20:12:05'),
